{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_29","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba tests/conformance/features/daemon_routing.feature | sed -n '1,240p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Daemon Routing and Leases\n     2\t  The daemon routes tasks to built-in flows, enforces task and lease invariants,\n     3\t  and reconciles stale daemon state under `.ralph-burning/daemon/`.\n     4\t\n     5\t  # DAEMON-ROUTING-001\n     6\t  Scenario: Routing precedence prefers command over labels and workspace default\n     7\t    Given a daemon task with routing command \"/rb flow quick_dev\"\n     8\t    And the task has routing label \"rb:flow:docs_change\"\n     9\t    And the workspace default flow is \"standard\"\n    10\t    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    11\t    Then the selected flow is \"quick_dev\"\n    12\t    And the routing source is \"command\"\n    13\t\n    14\t  # DAEMON-ROUTING-002\n    15\t  Scenario: Valid routing labels select the flow when no command is present\n    16\t    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n    17\t      | rb:flow:docs_change |\n    18\t    And the workspace default flow is \"standard\"\n    19\t    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    20\t    Then the selected flow is \"docs_change\"\n    21\t    And the routing source is \"label\"\n    22\t\n    23\t  # DAEMON-ROUTING-003\n    24\t  Scenario: Malformed routing labels are ignored with a warning\n    25\t    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n    26\t      | rb:flow          |\n    27\t      | rb:flow:standard |\n    28\t    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    29\t    Then the selected flow is \"standard\"\n    30\t    And the daemon records a routing warning\n    31\t\n    32\t  # DAEMON-ROUTING-004\n    33\t  Scenario: Conflicting routing labels fail task creation\n    34\t    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n    35\t      | rb:flow:standard   |\n    36\t      | rb:flow:quick_dev  |\n    37\t    When the task is created through the daemon task service\n    38\t    Then task creation fails with \"AmbiguousRouting\"\n    39\t\n    40\t  # DAEMON-ROUTING-005\n    41\t  Scenario: Duplicate non-terminal issue task is rejected\n    42\t    Given a daemon task already exists for issue \"repo#101\" in status \"pending\"\n    43\t    When another task is created for issue \"repo#101\"\n    44\t    Then task creation fails with \"DuplicateTaskForIssue\"\n    45\t\n    46\t  # DAEMON-ROUTING-006\n    47\t  Scenario: Lease acquisition claims the task and creates a worktree lease\n    48\t    Given a pending daemon task with a valid routed flow\n    49\t    When the daemon claims the task\n    50\t    Then the task transitions to \"claimed\"\n    51\t    And a worktree lease is persisted under \".ralph-burning/daemon/leases/\"\n    52\t    And the task references the persisted lease id\n    53\t\n    54\t  # DAEMON-ROUTING-007\n    55\t  Scenario: Reconciliation fails claimed tasks with stale leases\n    56\t    Given a claimed daemon task with a stale worktree lease heartbeat\n    57\t    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon reconcile\"\n    58\t    Then the stale lease is released\n    59\t    And the orphaned worktree is removed\n    60\t    And the task transitions to \"failed\"\n    61\t    And the failure class is \"reconciliation_timeout\"\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
