{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba tests/conformance/features/daemon_lifecycle.feature | sed -n '1,260p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Daemon Lifecycle Commands\n     2\t  The daemon foreground loop processes pending tasks, exposes status, and\n     3\t  supports abort and retry transitions for terminal recovery flows.\n     4\t\n     5\t  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-001\n     6\t  Scenario: Daemon start processes one pending task in a single iteration\n     7\t    Given a git-backed workspace with a pending daemon task\n     8\t    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon start --single-iteration\"\n     9\t    Then the daemon claims the task\n    10\t    And the daemon rebases the task worktree onto the default branch\n    11\t    And the task finishes in a terminal status\n    12\t    And the task lease is released\n    13\t\n    14\t  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-002\n    15\t  Scenario: Daemon status lists non-terminal tasks first\n    16\t    Given daemon tasks exist in statuses \"pending\", \"active\", and \"completed\"\n    17\t    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon status\"\n    18\t    Then the non-terminal tasks appear before the completed task\n    19\t    And each row includes lease and heartbeat data when present\n    20\t\n    21\t  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-003\n    22\t  Scenario: Abort transitions a claimed task to aborted and cleans up its lease\n    23\t    Given a claimed daemon task with a persisted lease\n    24\t    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon abort <task-id>\"\n    25\t    Then the task transitions to \"aborted\"\n    26\t    And the worktree lease is released\n    27\t    And the task worktree is removed\n    28\t\n    29\t  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-004\n    30\t  Scenario: Retry returns a failed task to pending\n    31\t    Given a daemon task in status \"failed\"\n    32\t    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon retry <task-id>\"\n    33\t    Then the task transitions to \"pending\"\n    34\t    And the task attempt count is incremented\n    35\t\n    36\t  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-005\n    37\t  Scenario: Abort rejects terminal tasks\n    38\t    Given a daemon task in status \"completed\"\n    39\t    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon abort <task-id>\"\n    40\t    Then the command fails with \"TaskStateTransitionInvalid\"\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
